1 Data Cleaning (Before Feature Engineering)

(a) Missing values 
Techniques:
Mean / Median imputation
Mode imputation                           toll simpleimuter , knnimputer
Constant value
KNN imputation
Iterative imputation


(B) Outliers
Methods:
Z-score method
IQR method
Noise removal

2 Feature Transformation

(A) Feature Scaling

Standardization
Normalization
Robust Scaling        Uses median and IQR for outlier-resistant scaling.


(B) Distribution transform       Used when features are skewed
Techniques:
Log transformation
Square root transformation
Box-Cox transformation
Yeo-Johnson transformation

3 Feature Creation (Feature Engineering)

(A) Polynomial Features       Creates: x,x2,x3       Used for nonlinear modeling.  
(B) Interaction Features      new_feature = height × weight   Captures relationships between variables.
(C) Binning / Discretization  Convert continuous into categories.  ex income → low, medium, high
(D) Date-Time Feature Extraction  From: 2026-03-28 to year , month , day, weekday , quarter 
(E) Domain-Based Features  These are manually engineered features based on problem knowledge. ex BMI = weight / height²

4 Categorical Encoding Techniques
Machines cannot understand text categories, so we encode them.

(A) Label Encoding        ex red , blue , green  to 0,1,2 
(B) One-hot Encoding      Creates binary columns.
(C) Ordinal Encoding      Used when order exists Low < Medium < High
(D) Target Encoding       Uses target mean to encode categories.
(E) Frequency Encoding    Encodes based on occurrence count.

5 Feature Selection (Removing Bad Features)
Goal:
reduce overfitting
improve speed
improve interpretability

(A)Filter Methods   Independent of model. 
Techniques:
Correlation threshold
Chi-square test
ANOVA test
Mutual information


(B)Wrapper    Use model performance to select features.
Techniques:
Recursive Feature Elimination (RFE)
Forward Selection
Backward Elimination


(C) Embedded Methods  Feature selection happens during model training.

Examples:
Lasso regression
Decision trees
Random forest feature importance



6 Feature Extraction (Dimensionality Reduction)
This is different from feature selection:
selection removes features
extraction creates new compressed features
(A) PCA   Transforms features into new orthogonal components.
Autoencoders

